.TH "zap_page_range_single" 9 "zap_page_range_single" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
zap_page_range_single \- remove user pages in a given range
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" zap_page_range_single
.BI "(struct vm_area_struct *vma "  ","
.BI "unsigned long address "  ","
.BI "unsigned long size "  ","
.BI "struct zap_details *details "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "vma" 12
vm_area_struct holding the applicable pages
.IP "address" 12
starting address of pages to zap
.IP "size" 12
number of bytes to zap
.IP "details" 12
details of shared cache invalidation
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
The range must fit into one VMA.
